p procurement organization oversees both direct procurement consisting of materials necessary for product development and manufacture and indirect procurement consisting of items supporting internal business operations it is managed within the companys indirect procurement processes the chief procurement officer is located in singapore it priorities •risk management systems within it systems supporting all business areas are being centralized and automated •gradually investing in modernizing it infrastructure •developing new digital marketing strategies is an important part of the companys long term business strategy  and previously unilever is a worldwide… moreit priorities •risk management systems within it systems supporting all business areas are being centralized and automated •gradually investing in modernizing it infrastructure •developing new digital marketing strategies is an important part of the companys long term business strategy  and previously unilever is a worldwide manufacturer of packaged consumer goods operating in asia africa north america the middle east western europe and latin america the companys products cover two categories food and home and personal care its brands include axe dove ponds suave vaseline signal snuggle surf slim fast lipton ben  jerrys breyers and country crock unilever is part of the unilever group owned by the netherlandsbased unilever nv and ukbased unilever plc the global cio who is located at the companys headquarters in london leads the it department at unilever another key figure in the department is the chief technology officer whose focus is on it architecture as well as global information security these top executives rely on vice presidents whose duties range from companywide initiatives dealing with sap to the provision of it services for example there is an executive in charge of information management who is dedicated to ensuring that the local and divisional level business leaders get financial reports with the level of aggregation appropriate to their level of responsibility other executives with a regional focus manage it for europe regional application integration and it for the ametcee region two of the vps and a director handle the provision of it services on a regional basis the vp of enterprise computing services is concerned with the data center initiatives in europe the vp of global it services manages service desk operations telecommunications and networks the director of global it innovation handles other aspects of it services and business partnering including agreements for application services the company relies on key outsourcing partners in some areas to manage these relationships the director of global services is involved with service delivery preparing and monitoring the contracts involves the director of global it finance whose duties include the financial aspects involved in preparing the outsourcing agreement but also in the benchmarking and performance monitoring necessary once the contracts are in place other it directors handle financial applications and strategic architecture there are also managers working on security architecture and sap services there is also a business application architect working with the cto and an it business partner for rd the company uses sap as its primary enterprise resource planning erp application and prefers off the shelf solutions to custom application development it works closely with its it service providers hp was brought in to manage data center operations in the americas asia africa turkey and the middle east unilever also has a contract with bt for the innovation and management of its supply chain the company works with accenture to implement a unified it platform for europe and relies on products and services from ibm and oracle in order to keep costs low the company recently implemented a microsoft private cloud infrastructure in which it uses windows server  r and windows server  and virtualizes those servers using hyperv technology estimates of the companys total it workforce near  with as many as  of its staff members involved with it professionals stationed in europe unilever us is maintained as a separate profile sector industry consumer goods consumer products manufacturers consumer goods food employees  revenue b fye  breaking news on investment signals date type inside scoop  staffing topic staffing databases company unilever plc london united kingdom opportunity seeking a consumer performance platform  database architect england port sunlight  staffing topic staffing data management company unilever plc london united kingdom opportunity seeking a consumer performance platform  automationinfra sme england port sunlight  project scoop topic mergers  acquisitions company unilever plc london united kingdom opportunity unilever plc has recently acquired hourglass want full access to this profile and more rainkings clients have access to over  new investment signals published daily which provide insights on spending initiatives pain points management changes and more from companies around the globe interested in becoming a client request a demo request a quote technologies currently being used it marketing data analytics databases big datanosql alteryxhadoophivenosql database business intelligence actuateibm clarityibm cognosibm cognos metrics managerjda reportingmicrosoft bimicrosoft proclaritymicrosoft ssasmicrostrategyms sql reporting services ssrs data modelingmining base sasca erwinholoshyperion essbaseibm spss statisticsjda demandmicrosoft ssissas data infrastructure cloud systems citrix netscalerf loadbalancersibm hacmpnodejsopenstack desktop virtualization citrix metaframepscitrix xenappcitrix xendesktopibm spvmware vdiworkstation email hosting mcafee mail servermicrosoft mail server data storage data backup emc legatoemc networkeroracle rman disaster recovery oracle data guard enterprise storage hds storageibm ess enterprise erp crm oracle on demandsales